Hello Adam,

We interrupt our regularly scheduled all-things-food-and-beverage to tell you that new speakers have been added to this cool series, "How to Build a Great Board" with Karyn Barsa. Guest speakers just confirmed include Allie Magyar, founder and CEO of Hubb<https://nam04.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Foen.us13.list-manage.com%2Ftrack%2Fclick%3Fu%3D6f81cb6174c9815102b0a379c%26id%3De34f4b5f85%26e%3D6bff5ad411&data=04%7C01%7C%7Cd5422a51e3164499cdf508d9302359ba%7Cce6d05e13c5e4d6287a84c4a2713c113%7C0%7C0%7C637593750675328277%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&sdata=sFjGt%2B7jrH0EhohiNLLITAcgbO%2F8ZYVPNgMzLe6kfac%3D&reserved=0>, Steve Davis, partner at Davis Wright Tremaine<https://nam04.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Foen.us13.list-manage.com%2Ftrack%2Fclick%3Fu%3D6f81cb6174c9815102b0a379c%26id%3D6699bb79a0%26e%3D6bff5ad411&data=04%7C01%7C%7Cd5422a51e3164499cdf508d9302359ba%7Cce6d05e13c5e4d6287a84c4a2713c113%7C0%7C0%7C637593750675328277%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&sdata=%2FRHNFjdSJUFf8v2t05liHnG%2BQjk4ZAx%2F1gFi3istggc%3D&reserved=0>, and Tyrone Poole, founder of NoAppFee.com<https://nam04.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Foen.us13.list-manage.com%2Ftrack%2Fclick%3Fu%3D6f81cb6174c9815102b0a379c%26id%3Db27990203a%26e%3D6bff5ad411&data=04%7C01%7C%7Cd5422a51e3164499cdf508d9302359ba%7Cce6d05e13c5e4d6287a84c4a2713c113%7C0%7C0%7C637593750675338267%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&sdata=KMcSqSEYO79ZEhiaQjO3gCo9DL702vZhvlv5lk0dnuY%3D&reserved=0>. This week's topic is whether/how to compensate board members, and next week is on how to recruit great directors. This series just keeps getting better as it goes, so we're opening registration back up! You can catch up by watching the first two sessions via video and then joining us this Thursday and next at 11am. Register here<https://nam04.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Foen.us13.list-manage.com%2Ftrack%2Fclick%3Fu%3D6f81cb6174c9815102b0a379c%26id%3D935bceff3a%26e%3D6bff5ad411&data=04%7C01%7C%7Cd5422a51e3164499cdf508d9302359ba%7Cce6d05e13c5e4d6287a84c4a2713c113%7C0%7C0%7C637593750675338267%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&sdata=2nLRAM6mXFPN16zy7FXhKYu16L2n%2B%2BCnwmXNi20zcYM%3D&reserved=0>.

I read on Twitter<https://nam04.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Foen.us13.list-manage.com%2Ftrack%2Fclick%3Fu%3D6f81cb6174c9815102b0a379c%26id%3Da5a45fd704%26e%3D6bff5ad411&data=04%7C01%7C%7Cd5422a51e3164499cdf508d9302359ba%7Cce6d05e13c5e4d6287a84c4a2713c113%7C0%7C0%7C637593750675348260%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&sdata=mxIcdeR9g4%2FyQVeOFvHqD30IfwlWaablX94bKMrVkgA%3D&reserved=0> this week, if you can comfortably afford a $100 dinner, you should be angel investing. While Twitter is a cesspool of information in many (most?) cases, this comment really struck me. I imagine many local executives in a wide variety of fields may not realize they already meet the definition of "accredited investor" and could be investing directly in local entrepreneurs right now. If this sounds like it could be you, please join us this Friday at 11am <https://nam04.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Foen.us13.list-manage.com%2Ftrack%2Fclick%3Fu%3D6f81cb6174c9815102b0a379c%26id%3Dab0acf747f%26e%3D6bff5ad411&data=04%7C01%7C%7Cd5422a51e3164499cdf508d9302359ba%7Cce6d05e13c5e4d6287a84c4a2713c113%7C0%7C0%7C637593750675358260%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&sdata=0x3rjLmZndnuLlA6oMPX2QFRYEjUc0Ja3KBSNXdlnDc%3D&reserved=0> for an info session on joining the Oregon Angel Food investor pool. Food and beverage is a fun category to start with because everyone eats! You've already got initial sector knowledge just by being human, and you'll learn the ropes to angel investing by doing it right along side experienced investors and those with deep F&B experience. If you happen to be new to town, it's also a great way to meet people and get to know the entrepreneurial landscape. Register here<https://nam04.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Foen.us13.list-manage.com%2Ftrack%2Fclick%3Fu%3D6f81cb6174c9815102b0a379c%26id%3D1dfb462259%26e%3D6bff5ad411&data=04%7C01%7C%7Cd5422a51e3164499cdf508d9302359ba%7Cce6d05e13c5e4d6287a84c4a2713c113%7C0%7C0%7C637593750675358260%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&sdata=JBR%2FvCpJlRzkcfH7xP37y9G0zOkZ0EUwXgv2VQLKn1Y%3D&reserved=0> to learn more, no commitment required.

Save the date! The interactive OregonAF Grand Finale & Marketplace will be September 17th, 1-3:30pm. Taster's Tickets (which include an amazing gift basket of Maker samples) will go on sale in August.

Cheers,
Amanda

Post Date: 06/15/2021 12:14 PM 
Affordable Housing Advisory Committee opening 

The City is seeking applicants to fill one position on the Affordable Housing Advisory Committee. Bend’s Affordable Housing Advisory Committee members are appointed by City Council for three-year terms. This Committee provides policy, code and funding recommendations to the City Council in alignment with the goals outlined in the City’s Consolidated Plan [ https://www.bendoregon.gov/home/showpublisheddocument/41581/636936763828630000?medium=email&source=govdelivery ]. 

 

Committee members are expected to have a high degree of technical expertise in affordable housing development or operation, or services that accompany affordable housing operation, or to have lived experience in poverty or affordable housing. Consideration shall be given to include representatives of the various geographical parts of the City of Bend and to those with lived experience in affordable housing.

 

Applicants must live in the City of Bend. Applications will be accepted until 5 p.m. on Friday, July 16, 2021. To apply for the Affordable Housing Advisory Committee to go: _www.bendoregon.gov/committees_ [ http://www.bendoregon.gov/committees?medium=email&source=govdelivery ]. Scroll down to “Advisory Committee Application [ http://www.bendoregon.gov/government/committees/apply?medium=email&source=govdelivery ].”

 

For questions about serving on the Affordable Housing Advisory Committee, please contact Lynne McConnell at 541-388-5514 or lmcconnell@bendoregon.gov.

 

For more information regarding the Affordable Housing Advisory Committee visit the web site at:

www.bendoregon.gov/government/committees/affordable-housing-advisory-committee [ http://www.bendoregon.gov/government/committees/affordable-housing-advisory-committee?medium=email&source=govdelivery ]

 

For more information about the City’s affordable housing programs: www.bendoregon.gov/affordablehousing [ http://For%20more%20information%20about%20the%20City%E2%80%99s%20affordable%20housing%20programs:%20www.bendoregon.gov/affordablehousing ].
